result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeremy N. Wojan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jeremy N. Wojan in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF135, 15TR649, 15TR691 @ 9:24 a.m. Agreement stated - pursuant to plea, State moves to  amend ct 1 to delete 2nd+ offense, statute stays the same but misd. Ct 1 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA and follow through, counseling deemed necessary, court costs. Ct 2 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA, cc, plead to OWI 1st, 15TR691 dismiss.  $1020 fine and costs (includes IID surcharge), 7 month rev.  Atty Laufenberg and Def agree. Plea quest. reviewed. Court grants motion to amend ct 1. No contest plea. Ct 2 - no contest plea. 15TR649 - no contest. 15TR691 dismissed on County's motion. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Laufenberg satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of possess THC, and possess drug paraphernalia. And guilty of 15TR649. Sentencing remarks by Counsel. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. No victim rights issues. Restitution on OWI already paid. Court approves agreement. 15CF135 ct 1 - sentence withheld, 1 yr probation - AODA, counseling deemed appropriate, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge. Ct 2 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, concurrent, same conditions. No credit if revoked. Apply bond. Postconviction rights. 16TR649 - $1020 fine and costs, 7 months revocation, retroactive to any admin. revocation, 1 yr IID upon application, alcohol assessment. Court amends OWI to >.15. pmt plan.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Statement by Atty Laufenberg. Court will leave AODA on 15CF135 to agent's discretion.

Defendant Jeremy N. Wojan in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 15CF135 15TR649 & 15TR691 @ 3:10 pm.   Atty Laufenberg is not representing. Not Guilty plea on both traffic citations. 15CF135 Waiver of Preliminary Examination Filed.  Atty Laufenberg agrees to waive p.h.   Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing.  Court accepts waiver and binds over. Information Filed. Atty Laufenberg has copy of information. Bond continued. County Traffic citations to follow.  Arraignment scheduled for February 24, 2016 at 09:30 am.

Defendant Jeremy N. Wojan in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15CF135, 15TR649, 15TR691 @ 3:33 p.m. Statement by Atty Laufenberg prior to going on the record. Preliminary hrg requested. Traffic cases to track along. Bond continues.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for January 5, 2016 at 02:15 pm.
No use of alcohol. No driving a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license.

Defendant Jeremy N. Wojan in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court calls 15TR691, 15TR649 & 15CF135  @ 3:24 pm.  Not Guilty plea on traffic citations & continue to follow criminal matter. Atty Laufenberg has copy of complaint, waives reading, & waives time limits for p.h. Court has already received not guilty pleas on traffic case.  Def. waives time limits for p.h. Court accepts waiver for time limits.State heard on bond.  Atty Laufenberg heard on bond conditions.  Court orders $200.00 cash bond, already posted, w/conditions.  Status conference scheduled for November 4, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
